{
  "stem": "10818.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they lived in the attic.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, as in all European places, the help lives in the--",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was one called Lena.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She's the only one I can remember.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I-- there may have been others, but I don't remember them very well.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, depends what you call formal Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In-- in Germany, there is a requirement that all school children take a-- a-- a religious education.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this still holds, incidentally.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was, for four years, in the-- in primary school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This is-- that's the-- the-- the-- the German way.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and-- and I was in a-- a regular primary school from 1930 to-- this was a-- a municipal school.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Called Schiller Schule, after the poet, Schiller.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "S-C-H-I-L-L-E-R Schule.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had the same teacher throughout four years.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In-- ?] in fact, she may have stayed on and taught them even-- taught the-- the people who remained in that particular school even longer.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because they were very attached to her.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I've recently heard from some-- some of the-- my former classmates, whom I can't remember, incidentally.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But then, in 1934, the usual thing is if you wanted to go and have an academic education, you would change over to a gymnasium or something of the sort.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in-- in Germany, in this case, it was called [GERMAN], [? higher ?] daughters' school.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, you know, not higher daughters, but school-- higher-- higher school for daughters.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was an all-girls' school at the time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was required by the authorities to take an entrance examination there, even though my grades did not warrant an entrance examination.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my parents felt immediately that this was put in for a Jewish child.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
